717760f.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 166th Street (West)
717760f.text:
Broadway, west side, north from and including West 166th (foreground),
to and including West 168th (extreme right) Streets, showing Columbia-
Presbyterian Medical Center. The prominent building (center) is the
Babies Hospital; on its right, Vanderbilt Clinic; and on its left, Pres-
bvterian Hospital (Sloane Hospital). On the extreme left appears the
Preabvterian School for Nursing, between Fort Washington Ave., and
Riverside Drive.
1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Writers Project.

717761f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 166th Street (West)
717761f-a.text:
Broadway, between West 166th (left) and 168th Streets, as seen from
St. Nicholas Ave. and across that triangular area known as Mitchell
Sduare. Prominent structures shown are units of Columbia University-
Presbyterian Medical Center which occupy that land west of Broadway to
Riverside Drive, from West 165th to 168th Streets. The Babies Hospital
occupies the center of this view.
June 15, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
